Sam Allardyce claims Arsene Wenger is the ultimate manager as he prepares to take on Arsenal on Sunday.

The West Ham manager has the greatest respect for Wenger, who oversaw Arsenal’s move to the Emirates Stadium without sacrificing Champions League football.

Allardyce, planning for West Ham’s move to the Olympic Stadium in 2016, said: ‘He’s been manager, accountant and financial director, there is no doubt about that.

